AB  - This paper is concerned with the measurement of welfare which takes into account both the size and distribution of income. An alternative approach to measuring welfare, which captures the sense of envy felt by individuals when they compare their incomes with each other, is considered This methodology is then used to analyse the extent and nature of welfare in Australia. The main objective of the empirical investigation is to measure the direct impact of Australian personal taxes and government cash transfers on the distribution of economic welfare by the size of income and by other household characteristics. The ‘Household Expenditure Survey 1975–1976’ forms the basis of the present study.
